      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BARWEN STORM (1) was severely checked and broke last start so forgive that result. Had looked close to a win when runner-up in his previous two outings, coming from wider to miss by a nose at this venue two back. The ace draw should give him every chance to atone. BURTON (2) has been coming from wider barriers of late and did a good job to win the last time he attempted this distance here two back. Major player from a much better draw. SOKYS FALCON (3) draws lower than last week and scored back-to-back wins last month, one of them at this venue. THE BANKER NZ (4) deserves respect after leading from this barrier for a last-start win by 8.5 metres at Leeton.",
